article.headline: Princeton 57, Iona 46
article.story: NEW ROCHELLE, N.Y. (AP) -- Justin Conway scored 12 of his 16 points in the second half and Princeton's 57-46 victory over Iona on Saturday kept the Gaels the only winless team in Division I. Kyle Koncz added 12 points and Mike Strittmatter had 10 for the Tigers (8-4). Anthony Bruin had 16 points and 10 rebounds for the Gaels (0-11). The winless streak represents the worst start in 62 seasons of intercollegiate basketball for Iona and is four defeats shy of the longest losing streak in school history. The 1974-75 Gaels started the season 4-4 before losing their last 15 games. Princeton was 10-of-22 from 3-point range while Iona was just 1-of-5 from beyond the arc. Strittmatter scored eight points and Koncz had six to pace the Tigers to a 32-20 halftime lead. Princeton led 50-37 after Koncz nailed one of his four 3-pointers with 5:05 remaining. Iona narrowed the margin to 53-46 on two free throws by Dexter Gray with 1:14 left, but got no closer. Gray and Justin Marshall each added nine points for the Gaels.
